Class AbstractAccessTypeProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
      • org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api.AbstractAccessTypeProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, IAccessType
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AccessTypeProxy

    public abstract class AbstractAccessTypeProxy
extends com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
implements IAccessType

    A data-access layer data-transfer object (DTO) lazy-loading proxy for the AccessType. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    A particular kind of access to authorize

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
